# Blade: Laravel component primitives (Acorn)

Applies alongside **`.cursor/rules/05-theme-php-blade-acf.mdc`** (data in composers, `@php` / `@endphp` safety) and **`06-theme-alpine-vite.mdc`** (no inline app JS).

## `$attributes->merge()` in components

Let consumers pass extra classes/attributes. In anonymous or class components:

```blade
<div {{ $attributes->merge(['class' => 'alert alert-'.$type]) }}>
    {{ $message }}
</div>
```

## Prefer components over `@include`

`@include` inherits all parent variables (hidden coupling). **Blade components** expose explicit props, attribute bags, and slots.

## `@pushOnce` for scripts/styles keyed per component

Inside `@foreach`, `@push` runs **N** times. Use **`@pushOnce('scripts', 'component-id')`** ... **`@endPushOnce`** (or the stack name your layout uses) so assets load once.

## `@aware` for deeply nested props

Avoid threading the same prop through every layer; use **`@aware`** for props provided by an ancestor component (Laravel 10+).

## View data

Shared data for views belongs in **View Composers** (`App\View\Composers/*`), **flexible** composers (`Composers/Flexible/*`), or **block** composers (`Composers/Blocks/*` — **`12-acf-blocks.mdc`**) — not duplicated across controllers (Sage has no classic MVC controllers for every view). Same rule as Section N in `05-theme-php-blade-acf.mdc`.

## Shadpine UI — `resources/views/components/**` (class components)

**Do not** use **`@props`** or **`@php`** in Blade under **`resources/views/components/**/*.blade.php`**. Those templates stay **presentation-only**: `{{ }}`, slots, structural `@if`, and composition of child components (e.g. **`<x-*.primitive.*>`**).

- **Defaults,** **`config('components.*')`**, **`$tw->merge(...)`**, attribute normalization, and any branching belong in **`app/View/Components/`**:
  - **Base class:** Shadpine class components extend **`App\View\Components\Support\ShadpineComponent`** (calls **`data()`** before **`resolveView()`** so **`$this->attributes`** exists in **`render()`** — Blade’s compiled **`startComponent($component->resolveView(), $component->data())`** evaluates the first argument first).
  - **Root tag** **`x-{name}`** → **`App\View\Components\{Name}\{Name}.php`** (class **`App\View\Components\{Name}\{Name}`** — Laravel resolves **`x-accordion`** via the nested fallback). Keeps each widget isolated under its folder.
  - **Nested tags** **`x-{name}.{sub}`** → **`App\View\Components\{Name}\{Sub}.php`** (e.g. **`Button\Icon.php`**, **`AlertDialog\Primitive\Trigger.php`**). Match Laravel’s nested component naming.
  - **Colocated helpers** for that widget → **`App\View\Components\{Name}\*.php`** (e.g. **`Calendar\ViewState.php`**, **`Button\ButtonClasses.php`**, **`AlertDialog\DialogCloseClick.php`**).
- **Rare shared utilities** (e.g. HTML tag allowlist) → **`App\View\Components\Support/*`** — keep minimal; prefer widget-local helpers.
- **No Tailwind utility strings** in **`app/View/Components/**/*.php`** — store class maps in **`config/components/{slug}.php`** (and read via **`config('components.*')`**); PHP may **`$tw->merge()`**, **`str_replace()`** placeholders (e.g. `{duration}`), and branch on props only. **Blade** may still use **`class="…"`** for static markup when no PHP merge is needed.
- In **`render()`**, return **`view('components.{path}', array_merge($this->data(), [...]))`** so **`$slot`**, **`$attributes`**, and constructor props are available in Blade.

**`App\View\Composers/*`** remains for **templates, flexible layouts, and blocks** — not for replacing component prop/view data for files under **`resources/views/components/`**. Detail: **`14-shadpine-ui.mdc`**.

## Fragments (optional)

For **htmx** / **Turbo** partial responses, `->fragmentIf(...)` can return a fragment instead of a full layout — only if the project uses that stack.

## WordPress + Blade

When mixing WP template tags with components, keep **escaping** consistent: Laravel `{{ }}` for simple values; use WordPress **`esc_html_e`**, **`esc_attr`**, etc. where the codebase standard expects them for i18n and WP APIs.

Skill: **`acorn-laravel`** (DI/config); **`tailwindcss-development`** for utility classes in component markup.
